post_text:
School Communication About COVID-19 to the Public
Because of federal guidelines the school district is restricted in communication about staff or students effected by COVID-19. After considering input from both legal and health organizations, the district will be cautious about releasing information regarding those impacted by COVID-19. Based on the best guidance, the district will only release information directly to the public when an individual who has been in the school facility tests positive for COVID-19. No individual will be identified and the notice will be general in nature to protect all those involved. Going forward, if a student or staff member is quarantined because of being just a close contact of someone who tests positive, no information will be released unless the person later tests positive for COVID-19.

No individual will be identified and the notice will be general in nature to protect all those involved. Going forward, if a student or staff member is quarantined because of being just a close contact of someone who tests positive, no information will be released unless the person later tests positive for COVID-19.

post_text: Yesterday the State Board of Education did not approve delaying the start of school. As a result, last night the Meade Board of Education approved starting school with students on August 20th. This is two days later than the original start date which allows staff more time to prepare. PS-K will not begin until August 24th. Enrollment information will be out next week. The district is committed to providing three learning models for students: 1) Face to face learning; 2) Remote learning if a student has to remain at home for a short time; and 3) An online program for those who choose to be solely at home.

post_text: Senior Graduation (July 26th - 3:00 pm) and 8th Grade Promotion (July 27th - 7:00 pm) are still planned at the MHS Gym. However, due to a recent increase in COVID-19 cases, local health officials recommended additional precautions be considered. As a result the Meade Board has added the following guidelines: 1) All participants will be required to wear masks or a face covering; 2) Those attending are limited to immediate families; 3) Individuals who have been in a hot spot or state that KDHE says requires a 14 day quarantine are requested to not attend. Thank you for helping to make this a successful and safe time for our graduates!

post_text: Friday, August 7th has been set for Meade 7th-12th students to take physicals at the MHS Gym/Locker Rooms. Rec. physicals for students in 3rd-6th grade playing football will also be available that day. Jr. & Sr. High sports' practices begin August 17th and students are not allowed to participate without a signed KSHSAA physical on file. Cost of each physical is $25. Students with a last name starting with A-M are to come from 8 AM to 12:30 PM. Students with a last name starting with N-Z are to come from 1-4 PM. Meade Medical Clinic staff will be completing the physicals.

post_text:
💜Teachers-We will line up in our vehicles in front of the elementary building prior to 10am. We will then “cruise” town to honk and wave at our students/families. Our parade will end when we arrive back at the grade school. (Feel free to decorate your vehicle, blare your music, etc.!)

💜Country kiddos/families-Feel free to come in and sit in your vehicles at the park or in front of a friend’s house and honk back!

💜EVERYONE- *We will be traveling roads that run north & south throughout the community!*

‼️We are excited to see our kiddos but remind everyone that we are doing it in this manner to continue respecting social distancing! Please do the same!‼️

post_text:
YIKES! My apologies to you regarding my Dr. Seuss Day reminder. Dr. Seuss Day has been cancelled.
I thought I was going to get ahead of the game, so prior to leaving for Spring Break I scheduled a Dr. Seuss Day reminder to appear at 2:00am today. Unfortunately, due to current events, our Dr. Seuss Day has been cancelled. Equally unfortunate, I forgot to remove the scheduled post. I know many people saw the post. Some sent DMs about it (THANK YOU!). I immediately deleted the post from our Live Feed, Facebook, and Twitter. Again, I apologize for the confusion.
Have a great day and stay safe,
Stacy Cordes
*This post is WAY to long to be a tweet, so hopefully our Twitter followers are FB and LF followers as well.

Even though school buildings have closed in Kansas, education will not end. A KSDE Task Force will release ideas today to help schools provide continuous learning. Kenneth Harshberger, Superintendent

post_text: This afternoon, Gov. Kelly announced schools would be closed until the end of the school year due to COVID-19. KSDE will give guidance soon on how schools provide "continuous learning" for students during this time. Offering take home meals is also something which may be allowed.

post_text: The Commissioner of Education, Randy Watson, along with the Kansas BOE, KSDE, KSHE and the Speaker of the House is strongly recommending all schools in Kansas close March 16th through the 20th. While Meade USD 226 is on Spring Break, the school will be closed for all activities.

post_text: Valentine Date Night Murder Mystery Dinner Theater - The Meade High School Forensics Team proudly presents "Dead 2 Rights" by Lee Mueller. At the annual meeting, Archetypical Corporation CEO Gordon Mullens believes profits are looking up. But the meeting takes a turn for the worse as the administration deals with technical difficulties, a double booking, and finally, a murder! Now, if only they could find someone to help solve the mystery. #MeetingsAreMurder. Come join in the excitement and use your detective skills to solve the case! February 13th, 2020, 6:30 pm in the high school commons. Dinner tickets are $10/person. Childcare services available for $3/child (kid friendly meal will be served). Contact Amanda Barnum, Lori Coles, or any forensics student to purchase a ticket (must be purchased in advance by Monday, February 10th).
